Author: gerymakgyaer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Building on Origin — Announcing Our Partnership With Origin https://publication.blocklancer.net/building-on-origin-announcing-our-partnership-with-origin-29d2d505f7fe    Origin Protocol is building protocols for the decentralized sharing economy. Origin believes that monopolistic middlemen have no place in peer-to-peer marketplaces. Origin wants to build open, fair, and censorship resistant technologies that allow people to do business with whomever they want without the permission of corporate rulers. Blockchain technology will have a profound impact on the global economy from how companies are started to how markets are organized.  The global Origin community of engineers are collaborating on the creation of a JavaScript library and a smart contract library. Origin does all of this open source development in public. Please join their Discord if you want to be part of these efforts. The ultimate goal of Origin is to empower anyone to easily build marketplace DApps. Origin has a fully decentralized live demo up on testnet as a proof of concept and a starting point for others to build on.  Over thirty projects have committed to building on the Origin platform.  We are pleased to announce that Blocklancer will be building the freelancing marketplace DApp on Origin Protocol. Blocklancer is a so called Distributed Autonomous Job Marketplace (DAJ) on the blockchain. Blocklancer is changing the way freelancing works for both the freelancer and the customer, concentrating on building a trustworthy platform all stakeholders can rely on. This is done by minimizing fees and introducing a decentralized tribunal system to guarantee every dispute resolution case is settled fairly. We are happy to be a part of the Origin protocol ecosystem.  The Blocklancer team has been aware of Origin for a while now. Origin already has a working demo and is building strong partnerships with many interesting blockchain projects that have a very high potential. We are happy to be a part of the Origin family and together we can build better decentralized products and can share important knowledge.  Stay tuned for more news from Blocklancer!

Author: Rekkom
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: You are in vain worried. That's what the team members said about this:  Quote Hello!  Thank you for the kind words, I'm sure the team at Blocklancer will be happy to read them.  As for your question. There was a soft cap and a hard cap for the ICO. The soft cap indicated the minimal amount of funds needed to run this project. The hard cap is the maximum and reaching it would make things a lot easier (more aggressive marketing for example).  The soft cap has already been reached 6 times over by now, so even if the hard cap isn't reached the project will go off as planned. The remaining unsold tokens will be burnt.  From an investor's perspective not selling out isn't a negative thing as long as enough funds were raised to launch the project properly and to reach its full potential, as a lower market cap implies a greater upside potential for early token buyers. On the other hand, more funds mean slightly less potential gains but at a possibly much faster rate.  Hope this answered your question.    And also as regards directly the question of the price of the token and the views of the developers themselves:  Quote As far as price predictions go, in the short term these are completely and utterly impossible.  In the long term (several years) Blocklancer could reach a market cap similar to that of currently existing sites as well as exceeding them due to their superior platform. Then there's also the massive growth in the Freelancing market that is to be expected in the coming years. A market cap in the $100m to $1b range would be small, which would equate to a token value of something along the lines of 70 cents and $7, or a 10 to 100 increase as a low end estimate.   I hope that these words will reassure those who are now worried or nervous. Calm down.  In any case, the money is already invested, the tasks are fulfilled .... We can only wait - it's now for the experts in their field   I hope my words were useful to you

Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: The ICO has been extended throughout March, so you still have plenty of time to participate. Welcome to the campaign.  Quote from: boty on February 27, 2018, 05:10:39 PM Hello bounty hunter,, There's something I want to ask you a bit about this bounty payment does anyone know the calculation of payments related to the stake? Every category has a total amount of shares. Your shares divided by the total amount of category shares will determine your percentage of the respective category. The category value is a function of the percentage listed in the bounty portal and the total amount of Ethereum raised.  If there's 1000 shares in a given category and you have 100 of those shares, you will get 10% of that category. If the category is worth 26% of the bounty pool it means that you'll get 2.6% of the bounty pool. The bounty pool is 2% of the total amount raised during the ICO.

Author: BTCMILLIONAIRE
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Your LNC tokens are a so called ERC20 token on the Ethereum blockchain. As such, you can move them freely between Ethereum addresses. Once Bitmart (or any other exchange) lists LNC on their platform you will be able to get an address to which you can send your LNC tokens for trading on an exchange. Using MEW this is pretty straight forward by selecting the tab "transfer Tokens" since you already have added LNC to your altcoins.  I highly recommend using MetaMask (or a hardware wallet such as Trezor or Ledger Nano S) for additional security with MEW.

Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: There's a project that essentially copied Blocklancer that turned out to be a scam (Coinlancer), where the dev team is holding something like 90% of the total coin supply, has a disproportionate amount of (fake) "advisors" (which you will never see in any real venture), lied about how much money they raised, refused to show their holdings, lied about their team members, spammed their own thread with sock puppet posts, repeatedly ignored and/or dodged technical and other critical questions about their "project", censored critical inquiry on their Telegram, and just up and vanished into thin air after the ICO.  The thread that you've linked was posted by a sock puppet created by said scammers.  If you check his post history and timeline you'll find that the account was created solely as an attempt at defamation as a retort of me exposing all the red flags regarding CL in their ANN. They falsely assumed that I was a part of the Blocklancer team, while I just exposed a scam like I'd usually would (refer to my post history to see that I regularly expose scams of different types when I come across them) and hence tried to attack this team as a result.  If you actually take apart the thread that he posted you should quickly see that it's a bunch of pointless accusations that are fully devoid of an understanding of corporate reality. Not to mention that resources are allocated within market standards. If the reasoning that this scammer provided was true that would turn not just every single ICO, but also every single traditional venture into a scam. And the facts are clearly aligned against his case.    Edit: I recommend reading the Whitepaper and the Yellowpaper (rigorous technical paper) if you're still in doubt. Both of which are far beyond market standards. And I don't mean from a writing perspective (the English isn't flawless), but from a content perspective. It's immediately apparent that this team has conducted extremely thorough qualitative and quantitative market research and successfully identified and addressed problems with the industry.

Author: BTCMILLIONAIRE
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hello!  Thank you for the kind words, I'm sure the team at Blocklancer will be happy to read them.  As for your question. There was a soft cap and a hard cap for the ICO. The soft cap indicated the minimal amount of funds needed to run this project. The hard cap is the maximum and reaching it would make things a lot easier (more aggressive marketing for example).  The soft cap has already been reached 6 times over by now, so even if the hard cap isn't reached the project will go off as planned. The remaining unsold tokens will be burnt.  From an investor's perspective not selling out isn't a negative thing as long as enough funds were raised to launch the project properly and to reach its full potential, as a lower market cap implies a greater upside potential for early token buyers. On the other hand, more funds mean slightly less potential gains but at a possibly much faster rate.  Hope this answered your question.   Quote from: lts_sml1993 on February 15, 2018, 09:17:58 AM 5534sig Joined the signature.  Welcome to the campaign!

Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Blocklancer token sale started on January 16 and will go until February 28 or until the hardcap reaches 10 million dollars. The exchange rate is 15,000 LNC tokens for 1 ETH. To date, 2,113 ETH has been raised, the softcap has been successfully overcome. According to Blocklancer business model, token-holders will earn on commission, which the project charges for transactions and additional paid services (such as allocation of vacancy).  The distribution of funds, according to Whitepaper, is quite standard - 78% of tokens have a public turnover, 20% goes to the team. Of all the projects that I've seen in the recruiting field, Blocklancer is a clear favorite.

I am even more puzzled to find out that when I listed my Blcoklancer tokens as future holdings, Cryptocompare already recognized it as LNC and gave it an ICO price of around .37 per token. This gives me a really good feeling everytime I look at it even though I believe this isn't yet the real price per token of Blocklancer. https://photos.google.com/u/1/photo/AF1QipPCv7ZnSS8C2mjGXRAC2x9BIVazae4af46enhOP  There's the reason for my puzzlement;  this price of 0.37 usd per token is actually for Linkercoin that have the same code LNC. Author: BTCMILLIONAIRE
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Dumpers are irrelevant, because LNC tokens will have an inherent value, as they entitle you to participating in the tribunals which pay out the profits of the platform among the token holding participants. So whenever tokens get dumped below their payout the market will be quick to sponge them up, especially once the platform matures.  Also, I do believe a burn was mentioned way back, but I can't find it in the papers anymore, so it's best to wait for the team to respond to this one.

Author: BTCMILLIONAIRE
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: And here another question from me regarding the platform and the THT specifically.  Will it be possible to "contract/hire" third parties to participate in the THT on your behalf without compromising token security? I'd imagine that very large holders would be quite interested in being able to contract others to work on the THT for them while paying them a share. Simultaneously people with no tokens would be able to earn some money on the THT without holding large quantities of tokens themselves.  This is something that could potentially attract more investors, while at the same time increasing the amount of voters on the THT to ensure fairly settled disputes. After all, hiring multiple people to vote on the THT while splitting up the total tokens among them would hedge against a loss of revenue due to "false votes" from voting individually on cases.

Author: BTCMILLIONAIRE
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: I'm mostly concerned about Ethereum breaking down again and causing delays for freelancers and clients. Or at least I was until I saw your calculations. If Ethereum doesn't upgrade its transaction throughput significantly, Blocklancer could actually end up congesting it on its own. With the Freelancer market growing at a rapid pace filling up 14400 jobs a day doesn't seem like a too outlandish target, especially if campaign managers ended up throwing their bounties onto Blocklancer to ensure that the people that join their bounty campaigns are of a high calibre. Fortunately that's still a few years into the future though, so by then ERC20 should be much more efficient than it is right now.  With fees being distributed to the voters, would that (in analogy) make the voters similar to miners on traditional PoW blockchains? E.g. with difficulty being the amount of votes, rewards being the amount of fees and hashrate being the amount of tokens held by a given voter?  Thanks for the Whitepaper, will be reading through it over the holidays.

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi,  - They describe themselves as micro-job marketplace. Blocklancer on the other hand is a complete freelancing platform and not just for micro jobs. - In Blocklancer you are able to pay freelancers in Ether but in the stor market you need to pay in their token plus you need to pay the gas in Ether. We decided to only use Ether for paying because of the wide acceptance of Ether and the simplicity to hold and obtain it. This way we further encourage the wide acceptance of Blocklancer. - They don't offer any utility (Tokenholder Tribunal) for their Token and neither any improvements compared to current freelancing platforms for the average user rather difficulties (their token). - Not very detailed whitepaper because the first four and the last six pages of their 20 page whitepaper are just filler and the rest doesn't contains any technical information. (Took them 4 months to create this) - Not very clear what they even plan to do.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: BTCMILLIONAIRE
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Been gone for a few days and noticed the last question regarding the LNC token utility aspect.  Are 100% of the fees going to be distributed among tribunal voters? Or is a part going to token holders in a way that a dividend would be distributed?  Also, since Ethereum had some major issues with that crypto kitty game (which only added 7~8 tx/sec to the blockchain), do you intend to implement further currencies for paying in the future if the slow transcations become an issue? The new Waves platform already supports over 100 tx/sec and can go up to ~1000 tx/sec, which is quite a leap from what Ethereum offers right now. Without a doubt the ERC20 blockchain will get upgraded down the line and you've already mentioned potential fiat gateways, but this in general still is something that is unclear to me.  Have the new technical papers been released yet by the way?

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, I don't believe that it is currently a huge problem because if I make a quick calculation. If we add 1 transaction per second to the Ethereum Blockchain we generate 86400 transactions (60*60*24) per day. On current freelancing platforms every job has at max ~3 bids which results in 6 transactions per job (1x creation, 3x bid, 1x accepting, 1x payout). If we divide the transactions per day (86400) by the amount of transactions per job we get the result of 14400 jobs per day. As comparison Freelancer.com currently handles ~8600 jobs per day. This proves very well that we don't need that many transactions as for example a decentralized exchange  .  All fees are distributed to the voter in the Tokenholder Tribunal to encourage voting on the platform.  Regarding Waves, it is currently no solution because they don't support smart contracts as of now but I will keep an eye on them. Other currencies are no problem to implement especially Ethereum Tokens.  The new whitepaper is already released you can find it here.  Thanks for your great question and best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Just a few more sentences to the value of Lancer.   A holder of the Lancer Token benefits from the Blocklancer platform in two ways.  - If you hold more than 10,000 Lancer Token you get access to premium features on the Blocklancer platform. After holding more than 10,000 Lancer Tokens for a period of at least 1 month your account will be automatically upgraded to a premium account.  - If you hold Lancer Tokens, you are allowed to participate in the Tokenholder Tribunal. For participating in the Tokenholder Tribunal in an honest and informed way you will be rewarded by a share of the platform fees. The benefits of the premium account and the participation in the Tokenholder Tribunal will be delineated in the following sections.  Premium Accounts  Access to premium accounts is restricted to Tokenholders. Only Tokenholders, who hold more than 10,000 Lancer Tokens, for a period longer than 1 month get access to premium features of the platform. This way we incentivize people, who are interested in the long-term success of Blocklancer. People, who are holding Lancer Tokens purely for speculative reasons and short periods of time, will not be able to use premium features. With the success of the Blocklancer platform the demand for Lancer Tokens will increase, on the other hand the supply for Lancer Tokens will decrease, because premium users will not sell their Tokens, because they would lose access to the premium features.  The premium account includes features such as: - Getting access to detailed profile statistics. Know, who viewed your profile and how you can optimize your profile appearance. - Only allow the best rated freelancers to apply for your jobs. Your job offers will be predominantly visible to the best freelancers on the platform. Freelancers with no rating or bad rating will not be allowed to apply for your jobs. - Your job offers will be higher ranked by our search engine. - Your application for a job offer will be ranked above non-premium applicants. - Get early access to new features.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, As stated it takes up to a week before your stakes appear. We need to query through all participants when updating and because of the huge limit of facebook api requests it isn't possible to make it faster. We could as well just give you 10 stakes after connecting (would be in less than 10 seconds  ). But we only give stakes out for actual shares and likes and checking this takes time.  To be honest there isn't much reason to make it much faster because everyone receives their tokens after the ICO anyways.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi,  Only Tokenholders, who hold more than 10,000 Lancer Tokens, for a period longer than 1 month get access to premium features of the platform. This way we incentivize people, who are interested in the long-term success of Blocklancer. People, who are holding Lancer Tokens purely for speculative reasons and short periods of time, will not be able to use premium features. With the success of the Blocklancer platform the demand for Lancer Tokens will increase, on the other hand the supply for Lancer Tokens will decrease, because premium users will not sell their Tokens, because they would lose access to the premium features.  The premium account includes features such as:  -   Getting access to detailed profile statistics. Know, who viewed your profile and how you can optimize your profile appearance. -   Only allow the best rated freelancers to apply for your jobs. Your job offers will be predominantly visible to the best freelancers on the platform. Freelancers with no rating or bad rating will not be allowed to apply for your jobs. -   Your job offers will be higher ranked by our search engine. -   Your application for a job offer will be ranked above non-premium applicants. -   Get early access to new features.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

The premium account price isn't planned to be dynamic because we believe that supporters from the first hour should be rewarded in the long run. Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Thanks for the great questions.    We decided to only allow 10 bids to reduce the amount of bids in total. If you think about it the chances of getting a job are always the same no matter the amount of bids. The only thing that changes is that there is more/less competition on every job. Another important fact of the 10 bids is that a freelancer shouldn't just mass bid on every job. Otherwise he could just bid on all jobs and cancel all he doesn't likes that much and thus only causes the clients trouble.  If a Tokenholder owns more than zero vote shares (see whitepaper) he is able to report a job offer. After this as with a normal dispute a single random vote group (see whitepaper) of the Token Holder decides about the job offer. If they come to the conclusion that the job is indeed spam it gets delisted.  To tackle identity theft we plan to integrate services such as uPort and similar services: uPort allows end-users to own and control their personal identity, reputation, data, and digital assets, securely and selectively disclose their data to counterparties, access digital services without using passwords; digitally sign claims, transactions, and documents, control and send value on a Blockchain, interact with decentralized applications and smart contracts, and encrypt messages and data.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Thanks for your question,  Most of your question has already been answered by our great community.    I just want to mention the advantages of hodling  the Lancer Token. A holder of the Lancer Token benefits from the Blocklancer platform in two ways. - If you hold more than 10,000 Lancer Token you get access to premium features on the Blocklancer platform. After holding more than 10,000 Lancer Tokens for a period of at least 1 month your account will be automatically upgraded to a premium account. - If you hold Lancer Tokens, you are allowed to participate in the Tokenholder Tribunal. For participating in the Tokenholder Tribunal in an honest and informed way you will be rewarded by a share of the platform fees.  After the ICO you are able to buy/sell more Lancer Token on exchanges.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: BTCMILLIONAIRE
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: I'm watching the video right now and a question came up to me.  What happens if someone decides to abuse the fact that the blockchain is incorruptible by either spamming the platform or something similar?

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Thanks for the great input. We definitely need to cover this topic better in our whitepaper.    Blocklancer integrates several measures to prevent malicious posts and spam. -   Every profile on the Blocklancer platform gets verified. (see KYC) -   We limited the amount of jobs that can be created by a single user within a certain timeframe. (120 seconds) -   Every freelancer only has 10 bids per week. (Currently in the alpha 10 bids per day) -   Blocklancer only uses the Blockchain as needed and thus we are able to prevent jobs from being listed.  Those facts combined make it very hard if not unfeasible to mass spam on the Blocklancer platform. On top of that we added features to prevent users from accidently spamming by client side checking the input of the user.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: BTCMILLIONAIRE
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: I don't really like it much either, since all the information could easily be found with as little as one to three clicks...  But from another point of view it keeps Blocklancer visible. And more attention means a more successful ICO for which pointless bounty questions would be a cheap price to pay. I can't really see any serious investors losing interest because of "spammers" in a naturally spammy forum either.   Quote from: Blocklancer on November 09, 2017, 10:15:07 PM Quote from: BTCMILLIONAIRE on November 09, 2017, 08:39:39 PM That's not what freelancing websites are normally used for.  But that is indeed a very nice idea that Blocklancer might want to consider expanding into! Having a branch that is specifically used to connect people with tutors for different subjects would be quite nice.   Not only would it increase the value of the token, but it would also give teachers, tutors and students a new platform to connect.  I'm sure the same problems that freelancers face today are faced by tutors as well. And since that technically does fall under the "freelancing" category it would be silly not to take advantage of that market and add it to the Blocklancer platform!  Hopefully the team will look into this. Hi, That's a wonderful idea. We already consider to add a fiverr like job offering system into Blocklancer as well. With that said it's not that hard to set it up for tutors as well. We just need to check out how that fits into Blocklancer (and how much demand there is).  We are currently working on a few extensions for blocklancer to offer everything needed to allow jobs to be paid hourly. But more to that in the next dev update.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team Unless I'm missing something, setting up a section for tutors should be as simple as "copy/pasting" what is already there and specifically promoting that branch of the platform as well. I keep seeing tons of flyers and job offers for tutors around campus all the time, so I would imagine that the demand would be quite large and that it would merely be a question of raising awareness (which may or may not be difficult/resource intensive).   When is the next update coming by the way?

So it's mostly not a new problem related to the blockchain.   We plan to make a development update every week from now.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, That really a great question. Should a draw or a close result happen both parties (freelancer+client) have the option to restart the dispute. Most likely the amount of voters was just too low for a valid result. We are also thinking about a higher instance tribunal to solve such disputes. (freelancer+client are able to execute it after the first dispute) Also note 90% of the disputes on current websites are very very easy to decide. (Freelancer hadn't finished the job, client doesn't marks the job as completed -> disappeared, Freelancer isn't responding, Freelancer hadn't completed the project before a milestone/deadline, Undeserved bad review from client/freelancer)  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Thanks for the question. On the Blocklancer platform freelancer are paid in Ether. We also plan to accept Tether(USDT) to reduce the risk of price fluctuations of Ether. Everything else would be just too big of a hassle for everyone involved. Many people already own Ether why should we use something else?  The biggest advantage of the Lancer Token is that the Token Holder receive 100% of the fees. On top of that the Token Holder are allowed to vote on disputes.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: BTCMILLIONAIRE
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Thanks for the responses. I had a hunch that that's what most disputes would end up being like, I just tend to like to think about the fringe cases before they occur. Very interesting to see some actual numbers about the dispute cases though!  What would the higher instance tribunals look like?   Quote from: Blocklancer on November 03, 2017, 05:25:24 AM Quote from: aalavandan on November 02, 2017, 04:09:30 PM those freelancers working through your platform, will they get paid in your tokens only? Hi, Thanks for the question. On the Blocklancer platform freelancer are paid in Ether. We also plan to accept Tether(USDT) to reduce the risk of price fluctuations of Ether. Everything else would be just too big of a hassle for everyone involved. Many people already own Ether why should we use something else?  The biggest advantage of the Lancer Token is that the Token Holder receive 100% of the fees. On top of that the Token Holder are allowed to vote on disputes.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team Have you heard anything about the US regulations that end up treating "profit sharing schemes" as "securities" and thus deeming them illegal, making them unlistable on some of the larger exchanges (in the US)?  And does this concern Blocklancer in any way or would the platform simply operate under a legislature where this problem does not occur in the first place?

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, There are multiple solutions for the higher instance tribunals. Important to note here is that not every dispute is viewable(voteable) by every token holder. This insures that in the very unlikely case that: Friend A isn't definitely able to vote for Friend B. Which is very unlikely alone due to the fact that friend A would lose LNC but this also solves unrational decisions by token holders. A higher instance tribunal could be that more groups of token holders are allowed to vote on it. Another option is that only the trustworthiest token holder are allowed to vote on a higher instance dispute.  Regarding the profit sharing. Blocklancer has the huge advantage that we give token holder a share for voting on disputes. We are in contact with lawyers because of this because we believe it is very important for everyone involved in Blocklancer to be on the save side.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Body: Blocklancer partnership with MicroMoney  Blocklancer is an official partner of MicroMoney. Together we can integrate the people from the “unbanked world” into the global market. Have you known that currently there are 2bln people, who have no access to financial services?  Many of the “unbanked” are living in Sub-Saharan Africa, the Middle East, South-East Asia and South America.  But there are even many people from the United States, who are unbanked or underbanked. This shows that being unbanked is not just a problem of the developing world. For example there are whopping 28.3% of US households, that are unbanked or underbanked.  MicroMoney is creating a system based on the blockchain technology that makes funding for people from the unbanked world possible. To achieve this they combine the most modern technologies: Machine Learning and Blockchain.  With Blocklancer the people from the “unbanked world” get the possibility to participate in the global job market. They can use the funding from MicroMoney to build a business and with Blocklancer they can find and pay people, who get jobs done.  MicroMoney and Blocklancer will bring new opportunities to the “unbanked”and together we can make the daily life of 2 billion people a lot easier.  https://publication.blocklancer.net/blocklancer-partnership-with-micromoney-18c6e8392ea6

Author: BTCMILLIONAIRE
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: It doesn't matter how large the coin supply is. If there was 1000 times more Bitcoins available but you could mine them 1000 times faster, the price would simply be smaller by a factor of 1000, but you'd have 1000 times more Bitcoin, so ultimately it's not going to be any different from now. So no, a supply of 1 Billion is not "bad". If you think so you don't understand crypto (or assets in general) and should take some time off to study financial markets and instruments instead of wasting time on this forum.  As far as a real price is concerned. I have certainly made some calculations for bad and good scenarios, but why should I tell you the prices? So you can outbuy me on the market even though you didn't do any research yourself?  Anyways, start by analyzing the market that the project seeks to address. In this case Freelancing. There is a lot of data about how big this market is. Then assume that Blocklancer gets a certain share of this market, make up your own mind about what you believe is realistic by researching available data for other freelancing websites. Then take that number and calculate it against the amount of fees that gets processed by the platform. Divide it by the number of tokens, and voila. You've got an estimate. This works for every project, takes more time and effort than reading this forum, but is also vastly more accurate and will allow you to outplay all the clueless people on the internet.  Good luck.

Author: BTCMILLIONAIRE
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Nice, that sounds very promising! I was a little worried that we'd end up losing a sizeable share of people due to not being able to go with fiat currencies, but it seems like you've got that covered as well.  How would the backend for fiat transactions work with regard to token holders and allocating shares of the fees? And how would the fees be allocated in general with multi currencies? Would everyone get a share of each currencies pool or will everything be pooled into one asset for "dividends"?

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Thanks for the great question. The fees are automatically distributed to the Token Holder in only one currency (ETH or USDT). Crypto currencies are internally converted after the payment process anyways. Everything else would be too big of a hassle for the Token Holder. We at Blocklancer try to make everything as simple as somehow possible. If it is too complex it is wrong.    Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Thank you for the interesting question  As you see in our roadmap, we want to fully decentralize the Blocklancer platform. Unfortunately there is currently no optimal solution out there to decentralize the data storage tier of  Dapps. Basically there is IPFS (as a decentralized filesystem), BigChainDB and Ties.DB, who are working on solutions to decentralize the data storage of Dapps. In our opinion Ties.DB is the most promising solution at the moment therefore we are cooperating with them to create a great solution for decentralized data storage.  Kind regards The Blocklancer Team

Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: There appears to be a copycat project called "Coinlancer". Not sure if the Blocklancer team is aware of them, so I figured it'd be a good idea to bring it to your awareness.  They don't seem nearly as competent though, considering they're just a poor rip-off that does not appear to be bringing anything new that is of any substance to the table.  Might want to put extra weight on the fact that Blocklancer has been in the making for quite a while longer and is thus far more likely to succeed during your ICO.  I won't be making any investments with them because I hate blatant rip-offs with zero improvements or innovation and will be advising any friends and family that ask me for advise to stay away from them as well.

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Thanks for mentioning,  yes we know about Coinlancer. Basically this is just a bad copycat of Blocklancer, which popped up from nowhere. I read their (not very detailed) whitepaper and there are some major differences:      They are not distributing the fees among the tokenholders     The fees are paid in their own token, which means that their platform cannot be used without their token     They have nothing about the platform online: no code, no demo, nothing.     They write that they will release the platform right after the ICO, which is suspicious (Why not before? We release before the ICO and already released a Demo before the pre-sale)     The whitepaper is not very technical and is not describing how they will solve anything in detail (the Whitepaper of Blocklancer is very technical and detailed)     They have no businessplan     They have no community(13 follower on Twitter!), I was also not able to find a BitcoinTalk ANN from them, they have no slack/discord/Rocket.Chat     They are not showing how much money was already invested  Coinlancer seems scammy but everyone should make his own due diligence.  Kind regards The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi,  yes we know about Coinlancer. Basically this is just a bad copycat of Blocklancer, which popped up from nowhere. I read their (not very detailed) whitepaper and there are some major differences:  They are not distributing the fees among the tokenholders The fees are paid in their own token, which means that their platform cannot be used without their token They have nothing about the platform online: no code, no demo, nothing. They write that they will release the platform right after the ICO, which is suspicious (Why not before? We release before the ICO and already released a Demo before the pre-sale) The whitepaper is not very technical and is not describing how they will solve anything in detail (the Whitepaper of Blocklancer is very technical and detailed) They have no businessplan They have no community(13 follower on Twitter!), I was also not able to find a BitcoinTalk ANN from them, they have no slack/discord/Rocket.Chat They are not showing how much money was already invested  Coinlancer seems scammy but please make your own due diligence!  Kind regards The Blocklancer Team

Another point, Ethlance has some freelancers on the platform but nearly none customers. You can check that due it is very difficult to see a rated freelancer. In Blocklancer they have a lot of prepared freelancers and even more customers thanks to their advanced marketing strategies. And the higher the traffic on the platform, the more it improves and expands."

Author: jobitcoin2
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Exciting new concept Explore the Blocklancer Platform here!   Every Investor in the Pre-Sale is entitled to be a Alpha-Tester  ICO Date   Winter 2017/18 TBA Price   10,000LNC : 1ETH and decreasing Max Supply   1,000,000,000LNC          WHAT IS BLOCKLANCER?  Blocklancer is a so called Distributed Autonomous Job Market (DAJ) on the Ethereum platform, our vision of a completely self-regulatory platform for finding jobs and getting projects done. It will change the way freelancing works, both for customers and freelancers, and it will lift the reliability of freelancing to new heights.  Find jobs Find jobs easily even without knowledge of what the blockchain is. You can search for jobs on our job market platform or build your reputation as a freelancer and get contacted directly by customers requesting your expertise. Simplicity is a core principle of this platform.  Get jobs done In need of getting a job done? No problem! Simply create a job offer at our platform and wait for freelancers to take you up on your offer or contact trustworthy freelancers directly. It's as easy as it gets!   BLOCKLANCER SOLVES ALL PROBLEMS OF CURRENT FREELANCER PLATFORMS With this project we want to tackle several issues that are currently prevalent in the freelancing world, including but not reserved to: fake reviews, getting the payment for your work reliably and the uncontrollable influence of a central authority figure.  Guaranteed Payment On Blocklancer you only have to pay if you are 100 % satisfied with the work or if certain milestones are reached. And in case of a dispute the token holders will decide. Never again will you encounter unilateral decisions by a biased authority and an unfair money loss.  Fair and Automated Settling of Disputes Never depend on a single authority to settle your disputes again. With our token holder tribunal (THT) the decision lies in the hands of thousands of token holders, guaranteeing a fair decision.  Low Fees Our fees are only 3 % per job, several times lower than on other freelancing websites. Freelancing will finally be a lucrative way of earning money - and reliable as well.  No Censorship Because of the blockchain, your job offers can't be deleted under any circumstances. Political Correctness and personal feelings play no role anymore, because the blockchain is incorruptible.    THE LANCER TOKEN The Tokens represent the share you have in our project. The Tokens are therefore comparable to shares in a company, where you receive a certain percentage of the companies revenue.  Token holders earn Fees 100 % of the fees earned from jobs on our platform will be distributed among the token holders.  Token holders keep the System running The token holders will be given a vote in our token holder tribunal, settling disputes between customers and freelancers.  For more information visit us on http://www.blocklancer.net  Update: Bounty I'm happy to announce the start of our bounty campaign and we hope to see many of you participating. You can find the rules here https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=1997477  Greetings from Austria    Translations: Russian Dutch Filipino French Italian Hindi Spanish Indonesian Polish Turkish Romanian  Social Media: Twitter Facebook Slack Reddit Google+ Github     █▀▀▄  █  ▄▀▀▄  ▄▀▀▀  █   ▄   █          ▄▀▄    █▄    █  ▄▀▀▀  █▀▀▀  █▀▀▄       ▀▄   ▀▄   ▀▄                         Freelance on the Blockchain                         ▄▀   ▄▀   ▄▀              [ Twitter ] █  █    █  █    █  █        █▄▀    █        █▄▄▄█  █  ▀▄█  █        █▄▄    █▄▄▀          █     █     █      The first Decentralized Autonomous Job market (DAJ)     █     █     █

Author: Somz1
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: I knew about this project but refrained from investing because it had/has so many red flags  1) The team showed only three people + two of them with the same last name 2) The Twitter profiles of the team were created just before they started promoting their ICO in July 3) "Join the 1 billion/trillion market" If you have a good project why put up such ridiculous slogans? These kinds of slogans appear when you cant back up the value of a project and rely on enticing slogans to lure investors 4) Now they are saying that they are conducting preico and an ico,while the fact is they already made an ICO,i followed all of it in August 5) They say hard fork difficulties didn't let them offer ICO in August,simply not true there were hundreds of ICOs going along with this 6) How could hard fork affect the ICO while the fact was they were accepting Ethereum?

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Blocklancer is the only platform completely dedicated to improving nowadays freelancing. With for example the Token Holder Tribunal (THT), decision making by the community, and many more. With that we really use the Blockchain as an improvement to the existing systems. This ensures trust between freelancers and clients. There are some someone could consider similar, but they are honestly completely different.  BitJob is quite different, because they describe themselves as "P2P Students Marketplace for Online short-term Jobs". In Blocklancer, it is not just about students and short-term jobs. We are a platform for ALL freelancers and clients and we employ methods (milestones) to also allow big-jobs on the blockchain.  StorMarket on the other side describes themselves as "micro-task marketplace economy". And at the moment it is totally unclear what they are doing at all, because right now there is no technical description of their platform available and also no whitepaper (on their website they state that the whitepaper is coming soon for about 6 weeks!).  The idea of Blocklancer and the technical solution is unique in every way.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: steamon
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Blocklancer seems to do hideous who the other developers are then listed on the website and they don't want to reveal their advisors. When we asked some questions they were pointing to their tokenmarket followers like we are hyped already why question our legality? That's not an answer and even a bad answer to give since it has the same hype as Monetha? I don't believe that. I don't want to be negative about the Blocklancer project I think it's a good concept. The reason we asked those questions is to receive more openness in the project since we are interested to invest into it but instead, I received avoiding answers. Indirectly I am giving you advice right now to considering giving more into to make it a better project so think about revealing those people. I have the right to research a project and I should not be really stumbling on the above if this is a serious project.  Also, I notice a lot of fake accounts joining slack with (Hallo Everyone) Then go into hiding and never reply again.  Note this is not an attack but something I stumbled upon and I wanted to get answers and I did not really get them that's why I am posting here. If you are doing an ICO everyone has to be open in a project. I mean cool that its a family project but it's better to reveal all advisors and team members like all other do.  Get all team members a slack account aswell.

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi Steamon,  I really appreciate your researching in our project There seems to was a missunderstanding on slack. We never meant that there are some hidden advisors. We are in talks with some people, but they are not our official advisors at the moment. We invited our subscribers to our Slack-channel. We cannot force anybody to be highly active on slack.  Thanks for your interest in our project  The Blocklancer Team

If not, how is that tracked?  Also, do we need to send the amount we previously contributed or can we contribute more at the 1:25000 rate?

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Thank you for your nice words!  Regarding Storm: Storm describes themselves as something for "gamified micro-tasks". So they are not really competitors of BLOCKLANCER, because Blocklancer is dedicated to the whole freelancing market. Moreover BLOCKLANCER solves multiple problems of freelancing on the web, like guaranteed payment, a trustworthy reputation system and dispute settlement and much more. If Storm is solving anything like that is unclear, because there is even no whitepaper around of them BLOCKLANCER had a whitepaper from the first day on and we are already working on publishing a demo-version of the platform.  Kind regards The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Dear supporters,  As you may have recognized, we are currently not able to reach the minimum funding. Therefore we decided to cancel the running ICO. We thank all early investors and all of them get refunded after the 5. September. If somebody doesn't know, how to get refunded, please do not hesitate to contact us via e-mail.  Blocklancer is a great and unique project, but the current situation is very difficult. We did an in-depth analysis, why it was not possible for us to reach the goal. The key point is that we had not enough money for advertising and therefore our exposure in media was not broad enough. Our social media presence is very high, but we were not able to reach out to the masses. Another problem is that the market situation is currently very problematic. Many investors are on holidays and many other people are still shocked by the Multi-sig hack and the CoinDash disaster.  We believe in the idea of a distributed freelancing platform and we have a great plan to continue.   In September or October, we will launch a pre-ICO (with max cap 500 ETH), where everybody has the possibility to get Lancer Tokens for the rate 1ETH : 20,000 LNC. Everybody who invested in the current ICO will get LNC for the rate 1ETH : 25,000 LNC. This way we want to incentivize everyone, who is a loyal Blocklancer supporter. Moreover we are creating a demo platform and every investor in the pre-sale will have the possibility to become an early-tester of the platform. The bounty campaign will be extended until the pre-sale ends and the participants will get 2% of the raised money from the pre-sale.  The money raised from the pre-sale will be invested in advertising for the actual ICO, which is planned in winter (maybe December or January).   We will also release an official Slack and Telegram channel very soon. We still think that the community is the most precious asset and we are always very happy to get constructive feedback from all of you.  We think that with this plan we can reach our goal to revolutionize the freelancing market and we are highly motivated to work on this project all day!   Kind regards The Blocklancer Team

Author: Coiner_
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Real projects like this don't even reach the minimum while the scammers people behind ACT fled with the money they raised in mere hours/days.   Does this sad news affect anything else? BCT signature campaign? Twitter campaign?

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi,  We are still very optimistic. We analyzed our campaign very extensively. We underestimated the value of targeted-advertisement on facebook, twitter, youtube, reddit etc. Other projects like ACT invest HUGE amounts of money into advertising before the ICO. We see that we have much more support of people than any other project and our community is still growing every day.  We showed everybody that we can do a super-smooth ICO. No problems at all - Everything secure and smooth. A pre-ICO is definitely the best we can do. The early investors will get the incentive, which they deserve and with the money raised from the pre-ICO we can setup a great ad-campaign and attract investors all over the world.  The Bounty campaign will not be affected at all. We extend the campaign until the end of the pre-ICO (September or October) and then all participants will get their share of the raised LNC. For the actual ICO which is planned in winter, we will launch a new Bounty campaign.  Kind regards The Blocklancer Team

Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Thanks for your criticisms @rasp. I accept responsibility for my mistake. I was only ignorant of the actual post being referred to and mistook it for post #1483 where I linked my forum profile instead of #1476 where I made my first comment on Blocklancer project. Thus, I edited the wrong post, removing the link to my profile instead. I didn't know that the address being referred to was the contract address in the post I quoted. I think I have done the right thing now. You can verify, please. More so, I am not trying to convince you that I'm new here because I don't think it matters much after all. It's your choice to either believe me or not. No evil intension whatsoever in my post to warrant being caught as you inferred. Apologies tendered once again for the mistake. Thank you. Wishing Blocklancer project a successful ICO. Cheers.

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi,  Thank you for your nice words. We made the smart contract very trustworhty so that everybody gets refunded, if the ICO minimum is not reached. We have no influence on this process. We are working currently on a demo platform so that more and more people get interested. The market situation is currently also very problematic. Many investors are on holidays and many people are still shocked by the CoinDash hack (All our supporters know that this could never happen to us ).  After the ICO (in September), we will come back with another crowdsale (maybe a uncapped pre-sale). With a demo, the evidence that our ICOs are very secure and the support of our community, we will then definetely attract much more investors. And with the money from this crowdsale we can advertise on much bigger platforms like forbes and coinmarketcap to spread our vision of Blocklancer to big investors. We are very positive that Blocklancer will be THE first big platform on the Blockchain, that is really useable for many people all over the world.   We thank everybody who supported us up to now and we hope that we can count on all our supporters also in the future.   Kind regards The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi,  Thank you for your advice. Currently this is not possible, because all funds are in the smart contract and cannot be accessed by us. Everybody will get them refunded after the ICO. We are planning to make a pre-ICO afterwards, to raise some money to advertise more on fb, twitter, reddit, coinmarketcap etc. As you may know we had no pre-ICO and therefore we have not enough money (advertising on these platforms is extremely expensive) to invest in advertising (we think this is the main problem, why the fundraising is that slow). We are also launching a demo platform in the upcoming weeks We are very thankfull for all the feedback and we are eager to implement it as soon as possible. We really appreciate our community and Blocklancer will be very big in the future!  Kind regards The Blocklancer Team

Again, i have nothing to do with BLOCKLANCER, i just happen to follow it as i usually do with ICO's and blockchain in general, but i never participate in any bounty or ICO or airdrop, ever. There are way to many ICO's going wrong in all the possible ways, but i would really hate to see this one go wrong!  The dev team has done an extraordinary job on this project so i would hate for that to go to waist, hell i have invested to much time following this ( the only thread on BCTT that i have read every post !), and i really hate waisting my time.  Sorry if this is to much, but being a network security nerd makes me quite paranoid in cases like this. Anyway, he mentioned twice that he will remove it, but he did not, that should be enough to ban him from the forum. And that begs the question: why is not he banned yet?

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Blocklancer definitely will increase in price when it hits the exchanges because we didn't had a pre-ICO, this way the value of the token is preserved instead of the usual drop that is more often-than-not characterizes tokens sold during pre-ICOs. We also think that not having a pre-ICO is a good thing for the investors. Selling tokens for dump prices can have enormous negative side-effects. For example one negative side effect of pre-ICOs is how early investors often sell at ICO prices once a token hits an exchange. In doing so, they still make an enormous profit and cripple the token’s price in the process. And there are also often transparency problems involved in pre-ICOs. So, we decided to not have a pre-ICO, because in the long term this is the best – for our token and for the investors.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Body: Hallo Michael, I had to register here since i have been following this project ( and many others ) since the very beginning. You did and are still doing a great job on everything related to this project, the idea is extremely good and very useful to millions of freelancers across the globe, and the level of project related info and support is top notch, leaps and bounds better that everything else i have seen so far. You have single handedly raised the level of expectation on the block chain as far as ICO's go! I will refrain from dwelling into details on why i think all the above, a quick read on your web site should be more than enough to confirm all of the above mentioned highlights. Mit Freunliche Grusse, Tom  P.S. One minor advice, i see no need for you to justify anything to those who come here with some ideas and opinions on why you do or do not do something as they would like, or as they see fit, or as they just think that is how something should be done. Theu should have taken the time to read your white paper and business plan. Requesting info on the project is all good and dandy, requesting info on your private life is.......well not nice at all. Private life should remain just that: Private.  P.S. to the above P.S. I am in no way affiliated to the project, i do not know any of the project developers, i will not participate in the ICO ( i never do ), I will be one of the users of Blocklancer for sure later on for a very simple reason: i am an expert on a lot of leading industries ( electronics engineering, large scale network administrator with work experience from working for United Nations and Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe, extensive experience in building, programing and using all types of CNC machines etc, Fluent in Albanian, Czech language, English, German and Serbo-Croatian, and less fluent in Bulgarian, Italian and Turkish language. )

Author: Lexycon
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Well, it's not my intention to badmouth ICOs at all - I know there is a lot of work in such a project, but i want to warn investors.     Business plan in 6.4. Legal Requirements: "Our company will operate from Austria, which means that we will have to comply with Austrian law. Most notably, we will have to pay attention to the E-Commerce law, which regulates businesses and transactions on the Internet."  There is no legal notice on your website. So you do not pay attention to the E-Commerce law.  Business plan in 6.3. Location: "We are currently doing all the work on the Blocklancer project based in a small-room office. [...]"  ... The only question is, WHERE is your office?   Summarizing, it is everything, but not transparent. Really nobody knows who you are. There is no futher information of your team in the internet. No company name + no location.

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, If we wouldn't be transparent we wouldn't have a business plan at all. I don't know what you have as if we made it a secret that we come from austria? The legal notice must be applied at the moment someone invests money into our project. It's common that you have to agree some terms in every ICO, before you see the address to send your fund to. Our office is in St. Johann in Tyrol as we mentioned earlier in a post (with proof).  Thanks for your interest in our project. Such questions are really important to create trust in our community. If you still have questions I'm glad to answer them.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi,  A faker is somebody, who pretends to be somebody, who he is not. Blocklancer is totally transparent. Our team is known, whitepaper is published, code published and even a business plan is published (can you tell me any other ICO with a business plan, because I don't know any). But as you may know, we are always here to answer all of your questions as detailed as possible. We absolutely understand that nowadays many users are very skeptic about ICOs. We are very serious here at BLOCKLANCER and we are doing our best to make this project a success for everyone (freelancers, client, bounty participants, investors and tokenholders). We are also super transparent: You can find all the information on our webpage or in the whitepaper. We even released our smart-contracts on git-hub. I think everybody, who seriously investigated about BLOCKLANCER or joined our bounty campaign, sees that there are many people putting their hearts and souls into this project and it is absolutely unfair to discredit these hard-working people without having any factual argument. There is lot of evidence out there that proofs that the Blocklancer Team is absolutely competent and hard working. If you investigate in other projects, you basically find nothing (sometimes even no whitepaper), except a big team with many (many) advisors. And regarding your concerns of young accounts you can also check here (nobody fakes such a account) to see that definitely not all accounts are young. Moreover it is not super-usual all over the world to have "high-leveled" linkedIn accounts. Here in Austria we have lots of professionals without having a linkedIn accounts. By the way, your BitcoinTalk account is also not a Legendary And an ICO should not be about investing in some twitter-accounts. It is about investing in new concepts and businesses with potential for the future. But if your investment strategy suggests to just invest in some old guys, who did 100 projects before, you will definitely miss a big chance (consider: you'd have also missed Google, Facebook, Twitter, paypal, Amazon, an much more). Having a young and highly motivated team is a big asset.  BLOCKLANCER is not a big show around the founders and advisors. BLOCKLANCER is also not the hundredth financial platform that makes everybody "rich" within seconds. BLOCKLANCER tries to solve a real-problem for many people. Many people have no access to the job market or are frustrated by the current freelancing platforms. BLOCKLANCER integrates many people into the job market and moreover Blocklancer improves freelancing by far. If you are interested, how Blocklancer works internally you can find everything in the whitepaper or if you are a coder you can even have a look on the smart contracts.  There are many projects out there, which are just talk and no action, but BLOCKLANCER is different. From the first day on we launched our homepage with a detailed technical description of the inner workings and we are nearly permanently on this forum, facebook, etc. to answer all your questions. We are also writing blog posts, create videos, etc. to bring our vision to the people.  If somebody thinks that Blocklancer is not legit, he must think that all ICOs are scam, because as mentioned above, Blocklancer offers far more than many other ICOs. The whole team loves to work on this project and we all believe in our idea of revolutionizing the job market. We know that it is not possible to convince everybody, but we are honored by everybody who believes in us and our project. We are very thankful for everybody, who supported us up to know and we are sure that with the help of our awesome community, Blocklancer will be definitely a huge success.  With appreciation The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: We released our solidity contracts on github. The contracts in the repository are meant to be a proof-of-concept. It demonstrates the feasibility of the whole Blocklancer platform. It already solves many issues involved in the freelancing process, including but not limited to: •   refusals of paying the agreed-on amount of money for a project, •   unfair decisions •   the uncontrollable influence of a central authority figure  Token Holder Tribunal The current implementation of the Token Holder Tribunal already includes major improvements compared to the voting system in current tokens (e.g. Augur). Another undesirable problem of the democratic implementations presented so far is definitely not technical, but social. During the voting period, running tallies are public. This leads to undesirable consequences such as bandwagoning and groupthink. Thus a successful voting system has to hide the outcome of the vote until everyone made their vote. In the Blocklancer platform everyone submits his vote sealed and has to unseal it after everyone submitted his vote and thus hides the result from the crowd. With this implementation, Blocklancer is really able to harness the wisdom of the unbiased crowd. In addition, Blocklancer doesn’t locks transfers of funds whilst a vote is active as other tokens do. Transfers of Tokens are always possible and at the same time we are able to tackle double votes.  Employment Contracts All Employment contracts are stored in a contract holder. With this implementation we are able to ensure the highest amount of expandability by adding the ability to support many different sorts of contracts. Another advantage is expandability and modularity by providing the option to seamlessly replace contracts of the system.  Migration to a new Contract The Blocklancer contract is designed to be able to migrate to a new contract in the case another standard (ERC20) should be established and thus makes Blocklancer future proof. With this concept Blocklancer is able to change every aspect of the platform at any given time just by asking the token holder to approve the change. You can find the source code on Github.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Quote from: Blocklancer on July 30, 2017, 03:27:29 PM Quote from: rasp on July 30, 2017, 01:59:53 PM hey i love the idea of this project but i am wondering how you expect to list on a us exchange from the way the SEC has dropped the bomb.and even if you list on foreign exchange US citizen's can still access this coin.and then again will a exchange even except this coin without being registered with the SEC.we need to clear this if no exchange will except the coin it becomes dust in the corner.and no i am not a US citizen but i would like to invest but i need to know where we go from here before i will invest i know you have a good project but hope you understand what i am saying.i personally think that the government metals into cryto world more then they need to but they want all the credit for doing nothing but trying to regulate something that they accually do not own but we will all have big stakes in here if it turns to dust is not good and the ico is comeing very fast and i think we need some guidence on this issue. Hi, thanks for your interest, The SEC ruled that some ICOs are selling securitys and therefore must be registered. The Blocklancer Token has far more to offer than a speculative value of a security for an investor. When you hold our Token you help in building and running a platform for Freelancers and Clients to be happy beeing around. The Blocklancer Token (Lancer LNC) is far more than just a simple token with no value. With Blocklancer you're involved in decision making and thus it's a utility token which isn't regulated. Therefor its absolutely no problem to get listed on exchanges. If it would be all Token/Coins (even Bitcoin) wouldn't be allowed to be traded.  Moreover the statement of the SEC was very specific to the DAO. By holding the DAO Token, tokenholders passively benefited from the investments of Slock.it (the company behind the DAO). This means that the DAO Token had absolutely no utility. It was just an investment in a company. The DAO Token was not powering a platform or anything else, therefore it is not a utility token and it is legit to see it as a security.  The Lancer token by all means is a utility token. The purpose of the LNC is to power a new generation of freelancing platforms. The Lancer token is absolutely not compareable with the DAO tokens. You can compare our LNC tokens to Augurs REP, which is also definitely not a security.  Many exchanges already said that they are just listing utility tokens and REP is listed on all of them, so there is absolutely no reason to think that LNC will not be listed on exchanges.  Best reagrds, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Blocklancer is the only platform completely dedicated to improving nowadays freelancing. With for example the Token Holder Tribunal (THT), decision making by the community, and many more. With that we really use the Blockchain as an improvement to the existing systems. This ensures trust between freelancers and clients.  BitJob is quite different, because they describe themselves as "P2P Students Marketplace for Online short-term Jobs". In Blocklancer, it is not just about students and short-term jobs. We are a platform for ALL freelancers and clients and we employ methods (milestones) to also allow big-jobs on the blockchain.   StorMarket on the other side describes themselves as "micro-task marketplace economy". And at the moment it is totally unclear what they are doing at all, because right now there is no technical description of their platform available and also no whitepaper (on their website they state that the whitepaper is coming soon for about 3 weeks!).  The idea of Blocklancer and the technical solution is unique in every way.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Blocklancer is the only platform completely dedicated to improving nowadays freelancing. With for example the Token Holder Tribunal (THT), decision making by the community, and many more. With that we really use the Blockchain as an improvement to the existing systems. This ensures trust between freelancers and clients.  BitJob is quite different, because they describe themselves as "P2P Students Marketplace for Online short-term Jobs". In Blocklancer, it is not just about students and short-term jobs. We are a platform for ALL freelancers and clients and we employ methods (milestones) to also allow big-jobs on the blockchain.    StorMarket on the other side describes themselves as "micro-task marketplace economy". And at the moment it is totally unclear what they are doing at all, because right now there is no technical description of their platform available and also no whitepaper (on their website they state that the whitepaper is coming soon for about 3 weeks!).  The idea of Blocklancer and the technical solution is unique in every way.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, thanks for your interest, The SEC ruled that some ICOs are selling securitys and therefore must be registered. The Blocklancer Token has far more to offer than a speculative value of a security for an investor. When you hold our Token you help in building and running a platform for Freelancers and Clients to be happy beeing around. The Blocklancer Token (Lancer LNC) is far more than just a simple token with no value. With Blocklancer you're involved in decision making and thus it's a utility token which isn't regulated. Therefor its absolutely no problem to get listed on exchanges. If it would be all Token/Coins (even Bitcoin) wouldn't be allowed to be traded.  Moreover the statement of the SEC was very specific to the DAO. By holding the DAO Token, tokenholders passively benefited from the investments of Slock.it (the company behind the DAO). This means that the DAO Token had absolutely no utility. It was just an investment in a company. The DAO Token was not powering a platform or anything else, therefore it is not a utility token and it is legit to see it as a security.  The Lancer token by all means is a utility token. The purpose of the LNC is to power a new generation of freelancing platforms. The Lancer token is absolutely not compareable with the DAO tokens. You can compare our LNC tokens to Augurs REP, which is also definitely not a security.  Many exchanges already said that they are just listing utility tokens and REP is listed on all of them, so there is absolutely no reason to think that LNC will not be listed on exchanges.  Best reagrds, The Blocklancer Team

Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM

Body: Hi, thanks for your interest, The whole freelance workforce has earned a combined revenue of an estimated $ 1 trillion this past year, making up a significant share of the U. S. economy. And that’s not all: The freelancing world is an ever-growing market with more and more people getting into freelancing every year.  The ICO is capped at 1 billion token.   Advantages of Blocklancer  Guaranteed Payment On Blocklancer you only have to pay if you are 100 % satisfied with the work or if certain milestones are reached. And in case of a dispute the token holders will decide. Never again will you encounter unilateral decisions by a biased authority and an unfair money loss.  Fair and Automated Settling of Disputes Never depend on a single authority to settle your disputes again. With our token holder tribunal (THT) the decision lies in the hands of thousands of token holders, guaranteeing a fair decision.  Low Fees Our fees are only 3 % per job, several times lower than on other freelancing websites. Freelancing will finally be a lucrative way of earning money - and reliable as well.  No Censorship Because of the blockchain, your job offers can't be deleted under any circumstances. Political Correctness and personal feelings play no role anymore, because the blockchain is incorruptible.

Author: Xavier59
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: I was reading the whitepaper and took a look at the Fig 6 (Client isn't satisfied about the freelancer work). It seems that if he isn't satisfied, it directly goes to the token holder tribunal. What if the client do agree that his work isn't sufficient ? What the point of going to the tokens holders tribunal then ? Can't the client and the freelancer think of a friendly resolution of the matter, with, for example, a reduced salary. This lead us to my second inquiries. The token holder tribunal seems too binary to me. Either it decides to give all the funds to the client, either to the freelancer. Are you planning to improve this system so that the client would only have to pay a given percent of the salary fixed at the start ? While your platform seems to be viable for $200 jobs, I'm not sure how good it would be for a $10k one.

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi,  Very good questions  Ad Question 1.) Of course the THT is just activated, if there is a dispute between the client and the freelancer. This is the scenario, where traditional freelancing platforms are failing. If there is no dispute between client and freelancer then there is nothing to decide for the THT.  Ad Question 2.) We discussed that problem quite extensively in our team. We think that you have to consider 2 main things here:  (1) What is satisfaction We came up with the idea that the satisfaction of the client is a variable and this variable can have certain characteristics. For example the satisfaction can be continous and bounded(0-100), or binary(true/false). If the variable is continous and bounded the client can be 100% satisfied, 0% satisfied or 2.5% satisfied and  every number in between is possible. If the variable is binary/boolean then the client is satisfied or is not satisfied.  If you look at a real world example to exemplify that. Imagine that a client wants a carpenter to create a chair for him. If the carpenter comes up  with a nice chair and the client likes it, the client will pay the carpenter for the chair.  This means the client was 100% satisfied. But what happens if the  carpenter creates a chair with 3 legs. The satisfaction of the client will not  be between 100% and 0%.  It will just be 0%. And also a chair with 2 legs, 1 leg or 0 legs will be not satisfieable at all. This should show that satisfaction is not really a continuos function. In most real-world examples satisfaction will boil down to being satisfied or not.  (2) When will the client benefit from the THT If we design the model in a way that it is possible that the client has to pay just a fraction of the price, it will become extremely attractive for the client to  call the THT every time, because the possibility is very high that the THT decides that he has to  pay less than the predefined price. Then the fees for calling the THT are much smaller than the savings from paying less.  Regarding your concerns for larger projects: For larger projects the milestone system is build in. This means that the client can split up a big project into separateable chunks of work (milestones or workpackages). Then the freelancer is paid for each workpackage separately. And the THT can decide on the milestones, if they are fullfilled or not. This also has the positive effect that the big project is better structured for the freelancer and the client and the freelancer is not at risk of getting no money at all for a big project. This is also connected to question 2 of course.  I hope that it is now a bit clearer for you  Kind regards The Blocklancer team
