Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, I hope that answers your question.   Creating a Job  The BPMN model in the Figure depicts the process of offering a job and bidding for the job. It can be seen that at first the client creates a new job. The client attaches a deadline to the newly created job. This means that the client has to select a bid before the deadline is reached. After job offering, freelancers are able to bid for the job. The bid of the freelancers contains the salary the freelancer wants to get paid for this job. When the client selects a freelancer and his bid, the employment contract is created. The employment contract binds the salary of the freelancer, so that payment of the freelancer will be guaranteed.  Process of finishing the work  Figure 2 depicts, that the client gets his ETH back, if the freelancer is not able to finish the job within the deadline.  Process of successful project  Figure 3 shows a successful project. The freelancer was able to finish the job and the client was satisfied with the work. It can be seen that the client is creating a review of the freelancer and the freelancer is able to create a review of the client. It is also possible to bring an unfounded review to the token holder tribunal. At the end of a successful project, the freelancer is able to collect his salary.  Client is not satisfied with work  Figure 4 shows what happens, if the client is not satisfied with the work of the freelancer. The client is then able to initiate a token holder tribunal. The token holders are voting, if the freelancer was able to accomplish the task or not. The token holders look at the job offer and the submitted work of the freelancer, to decide, if the freelancer was able to fulfill the job offer. Decision making is done by majority vote. It is considered that the majority represents the truth. If the majority decides that the contesting of the submitted work was unreasonable, the freelancer is able to withdraw his salary and the trustworthiness score of the client is decreased. If the tribunal decides that contesting was the right thing to do, the client will be allowed to withdraw the frozen ETH. In both cases the Tokens are redistributed among the token holders. Token holders that voted against the majority lose tokens and the lost tokens are redistributed amongst the voters, who voted with the majority.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Body: Hi, Thanks for your interest,  Token Sale Our maximum cap is 1 billion LNC and our minimum cap is 200 million LNC. During the first hour of the sale the tokens will be available at a rate of 15,000 LNC to 1 ETH. After one hour the rate changes to 10,000 LNC to 1 ETH for the first 10 million Blocklancer Tokens and this rate decreases by 1 % for every 10 million tokens sold. 10 % of the tokens will be kept by the developers and 2 % are reserved for the Bounty.  Usage of funds 35 % of the money raised from the sale will be used to improve the Blocklancer platform. 10 % of the fundings will go into general administrative purposes, 40 % are reserved for marketing expenses in order to improve the reputation of our platform and to increase acceptance of cryptocurrencies. 3 % will be used for our IT infrastructure and 2 % for all the software licenses needed. Author: plims
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: What is special about this project? Can anyone explain it to me in two sentences?

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Blocklancer is a so called Distributed Autonomous Job Market (DAJ) on the Ethereum platform, our vision of a completely self-regulatory platform for finding jobs and getting projects done. It will change the way freelancing works, both for customers and freelancers, and it will lift the reliability of freelancing to new heights. With this project we want to tackle several issues that are currently prevalent in the freelancing world, including but not reserved to: fake reviews, getting the payment for your work reliably and the uncontrollable influence of a central authority figure. The token holders will be given a vote in our token holder tribunal, settling disputes between customers and freelancers.  A bit more than two sentences but should answer your question.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: alexrums
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Why don't you limit the number of participants in the bounty? We can do this again penny for the bounty...

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, We just want to clearify that we give 2% of all issued token to the bounty participants which equals 300,000$ when completely funded with the low Ether price at the moment. Which is a huge amount compared to other Bounties. Meaning we may limit the number of participants if there are too many participants so no one receives much money which is still quite far away. Also note if more participate in our bounty we become more visible to investors which means we can make more money. If we make more money every bounty participant receives more LNC token. I hope you're satisfied with our answer. If not please tell us what you think is wrong.  Just wanted to add that you receive stakes per post. There are many participants that made 2-3 posts since joining. This increases your share in our bounty if you make a few posts per day.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team  Edit: The 2000 obviously aren't all signature participants they are the participants across all categories.

Author: BitMaver
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Blocklancer's Notification  Rule change! We think that your interest and active participation in our project should be rewarded with more stakes. We thought about increasing the stakes you additionally receive for posting in an official Blocklancer Thread (Translation threads included) from the very low +0.2 stakes to +2 stakes or more . But we don’t want to change the rules we made at the beginning without asking all participants. If we change the rule everyone will receive the additional stakes for the already made posts. What do you think about it? Should we change the rule? How many stakes would be fair? Why should we not change the rule?  I think it will be difficult in practice. Because it is necessary to subjectively rate each post and its importance. It is better to leave a fixed value stakes at 0.5 (0.2 is very small, 0.5 - easier to count). To prevent flooding, it is necessary to impose restrictions, for example: "Posts must be constructive and posts shorter than 80 Character will not be counted".  Or even abandon this idea.....you are already very popular and every day more and more. IMHO

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, and thanks for the kind words at the end.    Thanks for sharing your opinion with us. You're right you have a point there. It was our idea to start a more active discussion about Blocklancer and especially about freelancing over here with the increase of the received token per post. But you're right it could result in spam. 0.5 stakes per post is still a huge increase it's 2.5 times higher than now. Two stakes per post could really be too high But for now let's see what others think. As we said: "But we don’t want to change the rules we made at the beginning without asking all participants."  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Thanks for your interest, Who will be the token holders? The Token holder will be the investors and bounty participants in our project. How can we make sure the token holders will make a fair decision? Wrong voting is punished with loss of tokens which are distributed among the other voters. This will guarantee that one single authority won’t be able to influence this platform in their favor. A working platform is in the best interest of the token holders because their Token would increase in worth. In wrong voting they would punish themself (reduced Token price). It's similar to Proof of Stake.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi,  As you may know, we are always here to answer all of your questions as detailed as possible. We absolutely understand that nowadays many users are very skeptic about ICOs. We are very serious here at BLOCKLANCER and we are doing our best to make this project a success for everyone (freelancers, client, bounty participants, investors and tokenholders). We are also super transparent: You can find all the information on our webpage or in the whitepaper. I think everybody, who seriously investigated about BLOCKLANCER or joined our bounty campaign, sees that there are many people putting their hearts and souls into this project and it is absolutely unfair to discredit these hard-working people without having any factual argument. The team works extremely hard and everyday and brings new content to you every day. There are many projects out there, which are just talk and no action, but BLOCKLANCER is different. From the first day on we launched our homepage with a detailed technical description of the inner workings and we are nearly permanently on this forum, facebook, etc. to answer all your questions. We are also writing blog posts to bring our vision to the people.  If somebody thinks that Blocklancer is not legit, he must think that all ICOs are scam. BLOCKLANCER is really unique, it is the first attempt to bring a freelancing platform onto the blockchain. The whole team loves to work on this project and we all believe in our idea of revolutionizing the job-market. We know that it is not possible to convince everybody, but we are honored by everybody who believes in us and our project. Many things are coming in the upcoming weeks and we are looking forward to working together with the community to make BLOCKLANCER a very successful project.  With appreciation The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi,  Thank you for your interest in this project. We are sorry, but we are not having a pre-ICO. We also think that not having a pre-ICO is a good thing for the investors. Selling tokens for dump prices can have enormous negative side-effects. For example one negative side effect of pre-ICOs is how early investors often sell at ICO prices once a token hits an exchange. In doing so, they still make an enormous profit and cripple the token’s price in the process. And there are also often transparency problems involved in pre-ICOs. So, we decided to not have a pre-ICO, because in the long term this is the best - for our token and for the investors.   Regarding your concerns: Unfortunately, we are not able to give you an investment strategy around 1st August, but we hope that you will stay convinced of our project and maybe invest to make it even better. We have the conviction that Blocklancer solves real-world problems and this is what makes projects successful in the end.  Kind regards The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, thanks for your interest, Let's start with the first question, Blocklancer will be based on the Ethereum platform. I don't know if it's worth adding fiverr to the list, as it would still be the same, and they are as expensive as upwork with 20% fees if I am not wrong informed. But thanks for the hint, we might write a blog article about a comparison between us and fiverr. You can join our bounty campaign on our site.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: ciro1
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Great idea. Please make the escrow decisions on the platform very fair and less time consuming. I have worked on a tutorial site with this kind of escrow service, but the decision mostly favour the tutors leaving many students unsatisfied and even though they could get a refund, they usually lose a lot of time waiting escrow to conclude dispute. For example if I need a job done with a 48hrs timeline, and the freelancer spent 24hrs to do a bad job, then I dispute and had to wait another 24hrs for decision, even if I get a refund I have lost a lot in valuable time.

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, thanks for the link,  We looked into them and we found a few points that are odd. They don't have such a huge userbase, they are the devs of the Bitmaker app which is a great achievement, but has nothing to do with freelancing. As it stands, they just want to build a freelancing platform that is the same as the current ones and just bring it on the blockchain. I don't know how you feel about it, but we at Blocklancer think it is important to improve on current sites and not just use the blockchain to be 'cool'.  There isn't that many information about them, but as it seems their main points are:  - low fees (the fees (10-40%) they mention aren't even accurate, because there are plenty of freelancing websites which take less than 5%, we think there isn't even a single freelancer involved in this project otherwise they must know -> seems fishy to me). On the other hand, our fees aren't fixed but completely decentralized and controlled by the token holders who also own the complete blocklancer system and are able to adapt to current market situations by increasing and lowering the fees.  - They mention that they are all successful and earned lots of money but somehow they need to launch a super quick ICO without even having a whitepaper or even something to show off. If we had the money they already earned we would definitely make the blocklancer platform without another ICO why can't they, don't they believe in their idea? Seems very fishy!  - They only mention advantages for the freelancer, I as someone who freelanced a lot and talked with many clients, can tell you clients don't have it easy. There are many freelancers that don't make their work properly or don't at all. What do they plan, scare away all clients?  - and the blockchain   We think we made our point clear with the list above, but we would be interested in your opinion. We want to make clear that blocklancer is not only about low fees, it's about a high quality and simple-to-use freelancing platform that is completely decentralized and owned by the token holders (we give 90% of the tokens to the crowd). Freelancer care more about the platform itself and the clients on there, and not so much about the fee.  If the guys from Storm read this, I give you one important advice, freelance before attempting to make such a platform otherwise there will be many sad freelancers that lose a lot of their money!  best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, thanks for your feedback, We offer an escrow option for fixed price contracts. After a contract has been made, the client’s money is frozen until the contract is fulfilled by the freelancer. Should the client not be satisfied with the work of the freelancer, he has the option to ask the token holders to resolve their dispute and decide on who is right. The freelancer has the same option available to him in case he doesn’t receive his payment in time.  Best regards, The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Thank you for your constructive feedback!  Regarding the 200m tokens: You have to consider that the freelancing market is an extremely big sector in nowadays business. As stated in our whitepaper the  freelance workforce earned a combined revenue of an estimated $1 trillion. The tokens should be distributed amongst as many people as possible and should not be monopolized by a small amount of people. This way our token holder tribunal (THT) consists of many users and the risk of collusion and monopolization is nearly zero. You also have to take into account that Blocklancer will not be owned by a centralized entity, instead Blocklancer is designed to be a completely decentralized autonomous job market (DAJ) and is governed by the wisdom of the crowds.  Which issues do you exactly mean by scam and fraud related issues? I would appreciate it, if you can describe them in detail.  Regarding our team: We are going to show the people behind this project within the upcoming days.   Kind regards  The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: In general, after ICOs the price of tokens is determined by the free market. In the case of LNC, you have 2 sources of income.  [1] Steady revenue: You should consider that as token holder you get a portion of all the fees that are paid within the Blocklancer platform. This means that, the more active users there are on the Blocklancer platform, the more you will earn as a token holder. [2] Trading: Like with other tokens, you can trade your LNC.   Kind Regards The Blocklancer Team

Author: Blocklancer
Title: █【ANN】【DAPP】█ 🌟🌟🌟 BLOCKLANCER 🌟🌟🌟 ██ JOIN GIG ECONOMY BOOM
Body: Hi, Please do not use such words as "fucking"! We are all civilized here! And now to your point! That is just a freelancing platform where you pay with bitcoin. We on the other hand really make improvements to the whole business. If I freelance, I have to live from it and can't take customers that don't pay or rate me negativeley without reason. Furthermore, what is the advantage over let's say freelancer.com, elance and upwork? It just makes everything more complicated and doesn't solves anything. If you had read our whitepaper you would clearly see that we solve many issues of freelancers and clients and use the blockchain in creative new ways to simplify and improve things. It's the same from a clients perspective: no need to use it -> no clients -> no freelancers. There's no need to base your whole platform on the blockchain, if it doesn't give you any advantages over current centralized business models. And even if they were perfect in every way, why shouldn't there be competition? There are hundreds of freelancing sites which make millions.  Best Regards The Blocklancer Team
